{
  "schemaVersion": 1,
  "title": "Sajtmaskin model price table (USD per 1M tokens)",
  "description": "Canonical per-token price DATA (not just prose like 25-pricing.md). Read by scripts/db/generation-cost.mjs and the backoffice 'Generation Cost' page to turn logged token volumes into money. Prices are per 1,000,000 tokens in USD. Always re-verify against the provider pages before budget decisions — providers change prices.",
  "verifiedAt": "2026-07-09",
  "sources": [
    {
      "vendor": "OpenAI",
      "url": "https://developers.openai.com/api/docs/pricing",
      "note": "Standard/batch/flex/priority text-token rates. Verified 2026-07-09."
    },
    {
      "vendor": "OpenAI",
      "url": "https://developers.openai.com/api/docs/models/gpt-5.5",
      "note": ">272K input tokens => 2x input / 1.5x output for the whole session (standard/batch/flex)."
    },
    {
      "vendor": "Anthropic",
      "url": "https://platform.claude.com/docs/en/about-claude/models/overview",
      "note": "Claude rates mirrored from config/ai_models/25-pricing.md (repo reference). Not re-verified live in this table."
    }
  ],
  "unit": "usd_per_1M_tokens",
  "fx": {
    "usdToSek": 10.5,
    "note": "Approximate USD->SEK. Not a live rate. Adjust here (or in the backoffice UI) to reprice everything in SEK."
  },
  "notes": [
    "cachedInput is the discounted rate for prompt-cache HITS. Sajtmaskin does not log cached_tokens today, so the cost tools treat ALL input as uncached (an upper bound). See BUG-SWARM-BACKLOG / prompt-cache follow-up.",
    "Tiers: standard = default sync API. batch = Batch API (~50% off, async). flex = Flex processing (cheaper, slower). priority = Priority processing (premium latency).",
    "Codex-suffixed models (gpt-5.3-codex) are NOT on the public per-token pricing page and are billed via the Codex credit rate card; the value here is an ESTIMATE flagged with estimated:true.",
    "Regional processing (data residency) endpoints add a 10% uplift for models released on/after 2026-03-05 — not modeled here."
  ],
